'''Ramón Guzmán Carbonell''' (22 January 1907 – 1 April 1954) was a Spanish [[association football|football]] player and manager.

==Career==
Born in [[Barcelona]], Guzmán played for [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] between 1928 and 1935.<ref name="RGC">{{cite web|publisher=Mundo Deportivo|title=Galería de internacionales: Ramón Guzmán Carbonell|url=http://hemeroteca.mundodeportivo.com/preview/1988/07/20/pagina-27/1176038/pdf.html#|language=Spanish|date=20 July 1988}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/j/j11450.html|title=Player profile|accessdate=25 April 2014|publisher=BDFutbol}}</ref> After leaving Barcelona, he played for [[RCD Mallorca]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Mundo Deportivo|title=El Constancia batió al Mallorca por 3 a 1|url=http://hemeroteca-paginas.mundodeportivo.com/EMD02/HEM/1935/08/01/MD19350801-002.pdf|language=Spanish|date=1 August 1935}}</ref>

Guzmán made three appearances for the [[Spain national football team]] during 1930.<ref name="RGC" />

After he retired from playing, Guzmán became a football coach. He managed Barcelona during the 1941–42 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/l/l11450.html|title=Player profile|accessdate=25 April 2014|publisher=BDFutbol}}</ref>

